Judge Olu Stevens was sentencing Gregory Wallace to five years' probation after he and his accomplice robbed Tommy and Jordan Gray's Louisville home in April 2013 . 
  In victim impact statements the couple said their 3-year-old daughter was in constant fear of black men . 
  At the sentencing for Wallace , Stevens accused the couple of fostering racist stereotypes in their daughter . 
  He granted probation to Wallace and said his thoughts had no bearing on his judgement . 
  Friends and family of the couple are calling for him to be sacked . 
 